   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1818-02-22_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworth Town</placeName>
                  <date when="1818-02-22">Feb<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> 22<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. 18</date>
               </dateline>
               <salute>
                            Dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">Madam</persName>
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I have been negligent<lb/>
                    in not having sooner <choice>
                  <orig>acknow<lb/>
                        ledged</orig>
                  <reg>acknowledged</reg>
               </choice> the receipt of your<lb/>
                    obliging letter - and still<lb/>
                    more negligent in not having<lb/>
                    settled a little balance of<lb/>
                    account by which I am<lb/>
                    still in your debt <del>as I</del>
               <lb/>
                    £1 .. 17 - as I find by<lb/>
                    referring to your letter<lb/>
            </p>
            <p> I have requested <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntW1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Hunter</persName>
               <lb/>
               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1818-02-22_page02.jpg"/>
                    
                    to settle this with you &amp;<lb/>
                    I beg of you to accept my<lb/>
                    thanks - <lb/>
            </p>
            <p>There is no person out of his<lb/>
                    own family to whom it<lb/>
                    would give so much <choice>
                  <orig>plea<lb/>
                        -sure</orig>
                  <reg>pleasure</reg>
               </choice> to hear of a happy<lb/>
                    termination to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileJ1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Miles's</persName>
               <lb/>
                    affairs as it would to me<lb/>
                    - I trust therefore my dear<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">Madam</persName> that whenever<lb/>
                    you or he have it in<lb/>
                    your power to do so you<lb/>
               <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1818-02-22_page03.jpg"/> 
                    
                    will not delay to <unclear>give</unclear>
               <lb/>
                    satisfaction to<lb/>
            </p>
            <closer>
                    Yours very sincerely<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName>
               <lb/>
            </closer>
            <postscript>
               <p/>
            </postscript>
            <closer>
               <address>
                  <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Beinecke_1818-02-22_page04.jpg"/>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#HuntW1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>. Hunter</persName> for L £1.17.0 - on a/c of <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Miss E</persName>
                     <lb/>
                  </addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <title ref="./Workography.xml#Artic1">Article in Varieties in Monthly Mag Feb. p158</title>
                     <lb/>
                  </addrLine>
                  <addrLine>"Pay <persName ref="./Personography.xml#GrayX1">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Gray</persName> the Sadler -<lb/>
                  </addrLine>
                  <addrLine>"Bills to Smith Payne &amp; Co<lb/>
                  </addrLine>
                  <addrLine>"One Cask of Refined Coal Tar<lb/>
                  </addrLine>
                  <addrLine>To<lb/>
                  </addrLine>
                  <addrLine>
                     <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MileX1">M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Miles</persName>
                     <lb/>
                  </addrLine>
               </address>
            </closer>
